            <title>[SPR-1594] StringIndexOutOfBoundsException when calling PropertyAccessorUtils.getLastNestedPropertySeparatorIndex(&quot;x&quot;)</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-1594</link>
                <project id="10000" key="SPR">Spring Framework</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;There&apos;s a bug in org.springframework.beans.PropertyAccessorUtils.getNestedPropertySeparatorIndex(String propertyPath, boolean last):&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If last is true, the test in&lt;br/&gt;
  while ((last &amp;amp;&amp;amp; i &amp;gt;= 0) || i &amp;lt; propertyPath.length()) {&lt;br/&gt;
is always true, and if propertyPath contains no &quot;.&quot; dot, we never leave &lt;br/&gt;
the loop, and i eventually becomes -1.  A possible fix is&lt;br/&gt;
  while (last ? i &amp;gt;= 0 : i &amp;lt; propertyPath.length()) {&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;And then another tiny improvement: change the lines&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;  int i = (last ? propertyPath.length() - 1 : 0);&lt;br/&gt;
  while ((last &amp;amp;&amp;amp; i &amp;gt;= 0) || i &amp;lt; propertyPath.length()) {&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;to&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;  final int length = propertyPath.length();&lt;br/&gt;
  int i = (last ? length - 1 : 0);&lt;br/&gt;
  while (last ? i &amp;gt;= 0 : i &amp;lt; length) {&lt;/p&gt;</description>
